# KiLCA - Kinetic Linear Cylindrical Approximation

KiLCA is a plasma response solver using finite Larmor radius formalism for modeling the interaction of magnetic perturbations with tokamak plasmas.

## Compilation

Build KiLCA using the top-level Makefile from the KAMEL root directory:

```bash
make KiLCA
```

Or build all codes together:

```bash
make all
```

The executable `KiLCA.x` will be created in `build/KiLCA/`.

## Doxygen Documentation

To build the Doxygen documentation:

```bash
make doc
```

## Configuration

KiLCA is configured through input files in the run directory. See the KiLCA interface in `python/KiLCA_interface/` for convenient configuration management.
